Measure: proportion of ASPGN cases out of total GAS isolates
Focus_of_study: To identify the emm clusters from GAS isolates associated with ASPGN outbreaks
Notes:
148 GAS isolates identified (16 GAS isolates from APSGN cases, 18
isolates from APSGN contacts and 204 isolates from unrelated cases)
In total, 89 cases of
APSGN were reported from the Kimberley region from late 2013 until July 2015.

Disease Control (CDC) managers in outlying dis tricts to Darwin CDC.
